owl:Ontology.dc:creator: Haonan Qiu
owl:Ontology.terms:description: The purpose of the high-level map (HLM) ontology is: i) to represent the generic road knowledge for the autonomous driving functions, ii) to provide road environmental context for location-awareness and lane change notification via spatial reasoning, and iii) to support continuous dynamic map processes along a route.
owl:Ontology.terms:title: HLM: the High-level Map ontology
owl:Ontology.rdfs:label: High-level Map Ontology
